features: Extend Length You Want: This 4 Pole headphone extension cable with Mic which can extend your devices with a 3.5mm jack to the desired location for Audio & Mic. Compared with the TRS extension cable, it not only supports listening but also talking

Hi-Fi Sound: Great for voice chat in a game, video chat, live broadcast, listening to music, and singing, realistically restoring the original sound. 24K gold-plated connectors and oxygen-free copper provide maximum conductivity and durability, both designs ensure optimum sound quality after extending your 3.5mm device.

Protect Your Aux Port: This 3.5mm TRRS aux extension cable is a great solution to protect your 3.5mm aux port from repeat plugging and unplugging. It costs much to buy a new device, while it's so easy to get a 3.5mm audio cable

High-Performance Cable: The case of this headphone extension cable is made of premium metal material, durable and sleek. The braided outer of the 3.5mm extender is quite robust and flexible, making cables tangle-free and everlasting

Wide Compatibility: 3.5mm extension auxiliary cable fits all devices with 3.5mm port, compatible with iPhone 6S/6S Plus/6/6 Plus/SE/5S, iPod, iPad 2018(6th generation)/2017, iPad 4/mini 4/Air 2/Pro 10.5", Samsung Galaxy S10/S10 Plus/S9 Plus/S8/S8/S8 Plus/Note 9/Note 8/S7/J3, A8 2018/2017, A5 2018/2017, tablets, credit card readers (such as Square/PayPal), speakers, headset with microphone, MP3 players, receivers, car stereos, and more

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Extension Cable for Nintendo Switch Gaming
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the UGREEN Headphone Extension Cable 16 ft (THE 3 FOOT ONE WAS WAYYYY TO SHORT!!!), and I must say it has greatly enhanced my gaming experience with the Nintendo Switch. The cable length is perfect for my setup, providing the flexibility I need without unnecessary slack. I use it with a headset, and the microphone function works seamlessly.While I've encountered a minor inconvenience where I have to replug the cable for my switch to register, I suspect it might be more related to the console's hardware. Nevertheless, the overall performance and durability of the cable are impressive. The length is phenomenal, and the cable's sturdiness gives me confidence in its longevity. Surprisingly, it has avoided the tangling issues that plague many other cords I've used. Overall, a great investment for anyone looking to improve their gaming audio setup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I NEEDED this!
reviews.reviewText: I recently bought some IEM HEadphones, which have been game changer, yet, just like ALL headphones the AUX cord is short.This AUX extended the wire and I can now edit videos and game much more comfortably.I mention the IEM because they are high end headphones which beeds high quality wires to perform well with its 5 channels.This AUX cord works perfectly and did not alter the sound quality one bit.The cord is nicely braided and metal feeling, so it should last a VERY long time.I highly would recommend.Thanks for reading my ted talk

reviews.reviewText: Original headset cord couldn’t reach my PC. This solves that problem perfectly! No audio or microphone quality loss.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very good for an extension
reviews.reviewText: I needed an extra extension cable for some time. Like my other extension cable, I prefer to have a nylon braided cable because of its durability, and it doesn't get tangled when I move about. When I listen to the music, I can hear the bass tones (particularly jazz) quite well. I give this product 4 out of 5 stars (because I only have these for a short time).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got it to use for gaming headphones with a mic but after a few minutes the mic doesn’t work anymore unless I tightly hold together the connection between the headphones and the extension cable. Sometimes audio will only go to the right headphone or the left or will sound very muffled. I have to constantly twist the plug that’s connected to the cable and even then the sound is bad and it goes out after a few seconds.My headphones work fine when I cut the extension cable out of the equation. But I still need a functioning cable to extend the reach of my headphones.
Used as an extension for headphones with mic and it works perfectly. Very rugged construction. Nice looking as well.
Exclente calidad en los materiales y sonido.
